6:
Whoa! That one was so close,
I could smell it.
9:
It might be dangerous to continue
the investigation.
12:
So do we just go back and say,
"Sorry. Couldn't figure out why
the thunder's not stopping.
Better invest in some good earplugs"?
14:
They sure won't pay us for THAT information...
What do you think, Light?
26: It is the work of a dragon.
27: And I believe it's already sensed us.
33:
If it meant us harm, it would've
already attacked. We must try
and speak with it.
35:
Stay behind us, Stella.
If anything happens, run.
41: Wow... That's a dragon? It's beautiful...
44:
That form...
It may be one of the Ancients.
46:
Dragon! We have come
to parley with you!
52:
What sparked your fury?
Let us help you find peace!
57:
So you would rather fight than speak.
Very well...
62: Stella! I said to stay behind us!
66: I believe this dragon is asleep.
74: She's right. Its eyes are closed.
86:
The seasons have changed yet again.
Perhaps I have slumbered for too
long—even for a dragon.
88:
I apologize. It seems my sleep-talk
has stirred no small amount of
trouble.
92:
Wait, that's what was causing
the lightning? Your SLEEP-TALK?
96:
I used a great deal of power, tracking
down the champion. You saw me in
a weakened state, I'm afraid.
101:
Tracking the champion, you say...
Then you must be the
thunder dragon—Rams Euphoria!
106:
So I am. I feared I would not be able to
find you in a different world,
but it seems fate has brought us
together, Champion.
108:
And I have not forgotten you two.
Alk, Stella. It is a pleasure.
115:
Yes... In my dreams.
I have long awaited this day.
119: So... you can see the future?
123:
How did you come here?
And how will you return?
126:
The day you disappeared, the sky
wailed and the stars took on
strange forms. The Ancients leapt
into them and were transported
to distant worlds.
128:
The journey extracted a heavy toll
on the flesh. I cannot go by that
road again.
134:
Light, the World Flipper
will send you home.
137:
Will you not let me accompany you?
I daresay the services of a dragon
will prove useful.
140:
Stella.
I request leave to enter your world.
144: Of course. You are welcome, Rams.
148:
Thank you.
I had hoped to hear those very words.
152:
I had not expected to count a dragon
from legend among my allies.
157:
I am as surprised as you. For I had
sworn to never again come to the
aid of a champion.
159:
But as you are now... I can make
an exception. Together, we shall write
the ending to that dream.
168:
I will travel by wing. Let us meet again
in Starview Village.
172:
...And she's gone. Well, don't think we
need to worry about her getting lost.
175:
Oh, and I guess we can tell the Guild
we cleared up the thunder problem.
You guys ready to go?
178: Yes. I am right behind you.
186:
...Perhaps dragons truly are agents
of providence...
